                  <additions>
                     <p>On fol. 19v, the beginning of a hymn for Sunday, midlent, composed by the
                        Danish poet <name type="person" key="ThoKin001">Thomas Kingo</name> is
                        found: <q xml:lang="da">den ſom mig føder dett er att gud min herre mig
                           fattis <unclear>j alted</unclear> huad min nødtørft</q>
                        <note><bibl>Kingo <ref target="KingoSaml1975"/><biblScope unit="volume">IV</biblScope><biblScope unit="pages">339</biblScope></bibl></note>.</p>
                     <p>On the blank leaves, fols 4v, 5v, 9v, 10v, 15v, 16v, 25v, 26v, Bishop <name type="person" key="ThoVeg001">Thomas Wegner</name> wrote the names of
                        the deaneries in which the runic objects were found.</p>
                  </additions>
